<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="457" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,259,610]" pageId="2" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="457">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Anterior tentorial pit large, upper margin distinctly below a line connecting lower margins of eyes. Malar space approximately 1.5 × as long as basal width of mandible. Postocellar line 0.9 × as long as ocular-ocellar line.Antenna with 26 flagellomeres; flagellomeres with two sorts, distinctly longer and shorter setae. Prepropodeum (
<figureCitation box="[160,227,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1678,1702]" captionTargetBox="[175,1414,454,1653]" captionTargetId="figure-139@3.[173,1414,453,1655]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. Megastylus (Dicolus) mentouense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Male. 5 Mesoscutum and scutellum, dorsal view 6 Mesosoma, lateral view 7 Postscutellum, Prepropodeum and propodeum 8 Tergite 1, dorsal view 9 Tergites 2–3, dorsal view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848335/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="457">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) almost smooth, shiny, 0.33 × as long as total length of prepropodeum and propodeum. Propodeum (
<figureCitation box="[1360,1428,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1678,1702]" captionTargetBox="[175,1414,454,1653]" captionTargetId="figure-139@3.[173,1414,453,1655]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. Megastylus (Dicolus) mentouense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Male. 5 Mesoscutum and scutellum, dorsal view 6 Mesosoma, lateral view 7 Postscutellum, Prepropodeum and propodeum 8 Tergite 1, dorsal view 9 Tergites 2–3, dorsal view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848335/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="457">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) without transverse and lateromedian longitudinal carinae. Fore and mid coxae yellowish white. Mesopleuron (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[183,1419,631,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-176@2.[166,1420,631,1742]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Megastylus (Dicolus) mentouense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Male. 1 Habitus, lateral view 2 Head, anterior view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head and pronotum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848333/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="457">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[179,194,511,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1678,1702]" captionTargetBox="[175,1414,454,1653]" captionTargetId="figure-139@3.[173,1414,453,1655]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–9. Megastylus (Dicolus) mentouense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Male. 5 Mesoscutum and scutellum, dorsal view 6 Mesosoma, lateral view 7 Postscutellum, Prepropodeum and propodeum 8 Tergite 1, dorsal view 9 Tergites 2–3, dorsal view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848335" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848335/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="457">6</figureCitation>
) and mesosternum brownish red.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
