<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1874,2009]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="458" pageId="2" pageNumber="457">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,1875,1901]" pageId="2" pageNumber="457">Head</emphasis>
. Inner orbits slightly narrowed medially, scarcely concave near antennal sockets. Face (
<figureCitation box="[1247,1314,1874,1901]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[183,1419,631,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-176@2.[166,1420,631,1742]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Megastylus (Dicolus) mentouense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Male. 1 Habitus, lateral view 2 Head, anterior view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head and pronotum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848333/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="457">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) 1.3–1.4 × as wide as long, almost smooth, shiny; upper margin with median longitudinal tubercle; upper lateral between eye and antennal socket with weak longitudinal depression. Clypeal sulcus distinct. Anterior tentorial pit large, upper margin distinctly below a line connecting lower margins of eyes. Clypeus strongly convex, texture as face, 1.6 × as wide as long, median portion of apical margin almost truncate. Mandible (
<figureCitation box="[972,1038,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[183,1419,631,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-176@2.[166,1420,631,1742]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Megastylus (Dicolus) mentouense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Male. 1 Habitus, lateral view 2 Head, anterior view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head and pronotum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848333/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="458">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) small, basal portion stout, strongly narrowed apically; with two different teeth. Malar space 1.5 × as long as basal width of mandible, slightly concave. Gena (
<figureCitation box="[224,323,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[183,1419,631,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-176@2.[166,1420,631,1742]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Megastylus (Dicolus) mentouense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Male. 1 Habitus, lateral view 2 Head, anterior view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head and pronotum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848333/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="458">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
) smooth, shiny, evenly and strongly converging to occipital carina. Vertex and frons almost smooth, shiny. Stemmaticum distinctly convex. Postocellar line approximately 0.9 × as long as ocular-ocellar line. Antenna with 26 flagellomeres; flagellomeres with two sorts of setae, longer setae sparse, approximately as long as diameter of flagellomere; shorter setae dense, at most as long as 0.5 diameter of flagellomere; ratio of length from first to fifth flagellomeres: 10.5:6.4:5.8:5.5:5.2. Occipital carina complete, strong, joining hypostomal carina above base of mandible.
</paragraph>
